==English==
===Etymology===
*[[Diminutive]] of [[smile]].

===Pronunciation===
*SAMPA: /<tt>"smaIli</tt>/

===Noun===
'''smiley''' (''plural'' '''smileys''')
{{wikipedia}}
1. A simplified representation of a smiling face, usually as two dots for the eyes, a hyphen for a nose, and an arc for the mouth. '''<big>:-)</big>'''  Sometimes the hyphen is omitted '''<big>:)</big>'''
#:Often auto-"translated" to an image such as  {{Smiley|40}}
2. (''Internet'') A combination of keyboard characters used to gives a graphical representation of a person's mood or emotion, not necessarily a smile.<br>
3. (slang) Having one's throat slit from side to side.

